SIMPLE: glutinous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glutinous
<hw>Glu"ti*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>glutinosus</ets>, fr. <ets>gluten</ets> glue: cf. F.
<ets>glutineux</ets>. See <er>Gluten</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of the nature of glue; resembling glue; viscous;
viscid; adhesive; gluey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Havig a moist and adhesive or
sticky surface, as a leaf or gland.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glutinousness</ent>⟦br⟧
